name: Kollock
description: See 'Woodville Red'.

name: Kon-Wabisuke
description: Blackish Dark Red with Golden anthers and Pink filaments. Small, single cup shaped. M-L. (Japan 1937 - Hyôgo Prefecture).

name: Kona
description: White to unusual Greenish White. Medium to large, peony form. (Sport of Japonica 'Hawaii'). (For a variation of this cultivar see 'Maui"'). (U.S. 1969 - Hamilton and Clark Nsy., Upland, CA).

name: Kona Benten
description: White sometimes tinged Green. Small to medium, anemone form with fimbriated petals. Slow growth. L. (N.Z. 1990 - Haydon).

name: Korean Fire
description: Red. Small to medium, single. Compact growth with handsome foliage. E. Cold hardy. (Korea 1984 - Barry Yinger, Lewisberry, PA).

name: Korean Snow
description: Pure White with Golden anthers and Yellow filaments. Medium, single. Upright, open growth. E. Cold hardy. (Seeds from NW South Korea - Barry Yinger, et al - before 1986). (U.S. - Camellia Forest, Chapel Hill, NC).

name: Kosciusko
description: White. Medium to large, semidouble to loose peony form with upright center petals and intermixed stamens. Upright, compact growth. M. (For a variation of this cultivar see 'Kiandra'). (Aus. 1957 - Camellia Grove Nsy.).

name: Koshi-No-Fubuki (Blizzard Of Niigata)
description: Red. Small, tubular to campanulate single. (Mutation of a wild C. japonica var. rusticana). (Japan 1956 - Niigata Prefecture).

name: Koshi-No-Otome
description: Red. Medium, rose form double.

name: Koshi-No-Yoso'Oi (Niigata Adornment)
description: Blush Orchid Pink. Small to medium, formal double with small, rounded, shallow notched petals arranged in tiered or star shape. Upright, sturdy growth. E- M. (Japan 1970 - Mitsuroku Makino, Fuchû Town, Niigata Prefecture).

name: Koshiji
description: Red. Medium, single to semidouble.

name: Kosho-No-Reijin
description: Dark Peach colored whorls on a Milk-White background with Yellow anthers and White filaments. Medium, rose form double. Strong, spreading growth. M. (Japan 1979 - Hideyo Katô, Niigata Prefecture).

name: Koto-Hajime
description: White. Miniature, anemone form.

name: Koto-No-Kaori
description: Rose Pink. Small, single. Average, upright, lacy growth. E-M. Fragrant. (Japonica Tôkai x Lutchuensis). (Japan 1977 - Kaoru Hagiya, Niigata Prefecture).

name: Kramer's Beauty
description: Vibrant Red. Medium to large, full peony form. Vigorous, compact, upright growth. M. Fragrant. (U.S. 1980 - Kramer).

name: Kramer's Delight
description: Rose Pink. Large, full peony form. Vigorous, compact, upright growth. M. Fragrant. (U.S. 1980 - Kramer).

name: Kramer's Fluted Coral
description: Coral to Darker Coral at edge. Medium, semidouble with fluted petals. (U.S. 1983 - Kramer).

name: Kramer's Fluted Coral Variegated
description: Coral and White variation of 'Kramer's Fluted Coral'. (U.S. 1989 - Kramer).

name: Kramer's Supreme
description: Turkey Red. Large to very large, full peony form. Vigorous, compact, upright growth. M. Fragrant. (For a variation of this cultivar see 'Cucamonga'). (U.S. 1957 - Kramer).

name: Kramer's Supreme Variegated
description: Turkey Red blotched White variation of 'Kramer's Supreme'. Fragrant.

name: Kreena
description: Brilliant Red. Large, single. (U.S. 1953 - Smythe Nsy., Ross, CA).

name: Kristen Lynn
description: White with Yellow anthers and White filaments. Large to very large, semidouble to loose peony form. Vigorous, upright, dense growth. M. (Seedling of Japonica 'Gus Menard'). (U.S. 2019 - Jim Smelley, Moss Point, MS).

name: Kristie Wilson
description: Vibrant Deep Pink shading to White at center. Very large, rose form double. Average, dense, upright growth. M- L. (Reticulata 'Cornelian' seedling). (Aus. 1998 - J. and P. Wilson, Figtree, NSW)

name: Kristin Woodroof
description: Clear veined Pink. Large, semidouble with fluted, upright center petals. Average, compact growth. E-M. (U.S. 1964 - W. E. Woodroof, Sherman Oaks, CA).

name: Kristy Piet
description: White with occasional Pink specks and streaks. Miniature, formal double. Vigorous, compact, upright growth. M. (U.S. 1986 - Piet and Gaeta).

name: Kubal Kain
description: Ruby Red. Medium to large, loose peony form. Average, compact growth. M. (U.S. 1965 - Shackelford).

name: Kubal Kain Supreme
description: Variegated variation of 'Kubal Kain' - Ruby Red moiré White. (U.S. 1967 - Shackelford).

name: Kujaku-Tsubaki
description: Red mottled White. Small, single with slender, tubular petals. Average, semi-cascading growth. M-L. (Japan to U.S. 1977 - Nuccio's).

name: Kumagai
description: Dark Red. Large, single with flared White stamens which in most flowers are fully capped with Pink and White petaloids. See Higo.

name: Kumagai (Nagoya)
description: Same as parent except reported that stamens in all flowers are fully capped with petaloids. (Sport of Japonica 'Kumagai').

name: Kumasaka
description: ('Lady Marion'; 'Jeanne Kerr'; 'Maiden'; 'Sherbrooke'; 'Kumasaka-Beni'; 'Hollyhock'). Rose Pink. Medium, rose form double to peony form. Vigorous, compact growth. M-L. Cold hardy. (Japan 1896 - Tokyo Nsy.).

name: Kumasaka Variegated
description: ('Deacon Dodd'; 'Gay Boy'). Rose Pink blotched White variation of 'Kumasaka'.

name: Kumasaka White
description: White. (Sport of Japonica 'Kumasaka'). (U.S. 1959 - Hudson).

name: Kumasaka-Beni
description: See 'Kumasaka'.

name: Kuni-No-Hikari
description: Rose Red. Medium, single with flared soft Pink stamens. See Higo.

name: Kunming Spring
description: ('Kunmingchun' - Chinese Name). Deep Orchid Pink. Large, semidouble with irregular, upright petals. E. (Yunnan Reticulata). (China to U.S. 1980 - U. C. Bot. Gdn, CA).

name: Kunmingchun
description: See 'Kunming Spring'.

name: Kuro Delight
description: Maroon Red. Medium to large, semidouble form. Average, spreading growth with unique foliage. M-L. Cold hardy to -10°F. (U.S. 1999 - Ackerman).

name: Kuro-Tsubaki
description: Black Red with Red stamens. Small, semidouble. Average, compact growth. M-L. (Japan 1896 - Tokyo Nsy.).

name: Kurrajong
description: Cream White. Medium, formal double with pointed petals. Vigorous growth. M-L. (Aus. 1959 - Waterhouse).

name: Kute Kate
description: Bright Red. Small, formal double to peony form. Average, upright, open growth. E-M. (Japonica 'Edna Campbell' x unknown pollen parent). (U.S. 2009 - John L. Spencer, Lakeland, FL).

name: Kwan Yuen
description: Coral Rose. Large, semidouble to rose form double. Strong, upright, compact growth. M. (Reticulata hybrid 'Buddha' × Hybrid 'Coral Delight'). (U.S. 1981 - Charvet).

name: Kwan Yuen Special
description: Coral Rose variegated White. Large, semidouble to rose form double. Strong, upright, compact growth. M. (Reticulata hybrid 'Buddha' × Hybrid 'Coral Delight'). (U.S. 2009 - Charvet).

name: Kyle
description: Bright Red with Yellow anthers and Yellow filaments. Very large, semidouble. Average, upright growth. E-M. (U.S. 2013 - Howell).

name: Kyle Variegated
description: Bright Red and White variegated form of 'Kyle'. (U.S. 2013 - Howell).

name: Kyle White
description: White with Yellow anthers and White filaments. Medium, semidouble to rose form double; the edges of each petal have a notch in the center. Average, upright, open growth. M-L. (U.S. 2013 - Barbara Kyle, New Iberia, LA).

name: Kyo-Kanoko
description: Red. Medium, semidouble to peony form. Average, bushy growth. M. (Japan to U.S. 1930 - Star).

name: Kyo-Kanoko Surprise
description: Light Pink throat with tips of petals ringed with White. (Sport of Japonica 'Kyo-Kanoko'). (U.S. 1964 - J M Jones, Savannah, GA).

name: Kyo-Kanoko Variegated
description: ('Kyo-Ko'). Red and White variation of 'Kyo-Kanoko'.

name: Kyo-Ko
description: See 'Kyo-Kanoko Variegated'.

name: Kyo-Nishiki
description: (Brocade of Kyoto). White streaked and spotted Pink. Medium, single. See 'Higo'.
